  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC Epidemics 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">simultaneous outbreaks of yellow fever cholera and measles in DRC since January 2016. Ministry of Health declared official outbreak of yellow fever epidemic on 20th June. Measles and cholera outbreaks also declared in some health zones with a risk of spreading across the country. IFRC Country Cluster supporting the operations from Yaound&#xE9;. Recruitment of 3 delegates ongoing: Head of operations health coordinator logistics coordinator. BRC considering supporting the appeal through a disaster fund application of 80 000 CHF - earmarked funds to activities aiming to reducing the risk of waterborne and water related diseases in targeted communities (Kinshasa Equateur Mongala)</narrative>
  </description>
